OverviewExperienceNews & ResourcesHonorsOverviewJeff Miro is a seasoned corporate attorney with a particular focus on corporate boards, corporate governance, and corporate strategy, as well as on tax and family planning.
Experience Acquisition and sale of public and large private companies, including acquisition of the Irvine Company, acquisition of Sotheby's, and listing of Sotheby's Holding on the NYSE and London Stock Exchange Representation of The General Motors Pension Trusts (hourly rate and salaried) in the large financing of properties in White Plains, New York Assisted in taking public The Taubman Realty Group and Taubman Centers, Inc. (the first UPREIT) Acquisition of Woodward & Lothrop Department Stores in Washington, D.C. Acquisition and sale of numerous beer distributorships Acquisition and sale of major regional shopping centers Acquisition and sale of radio stations Acquisition and sale of A&W Restaurants and A&W International Preparation and administering large estates with values greater than $1 billion 
